        "product_description": {
            "value": "ParaLace brand 550 paracord hiking boot laces are built for adventure, made to be used and designed to withstand even the most rugged of outdoor environments. Sold in pairs, these paracord shoelaces are highly resistant to abrasion, weather, wear and tear, and UV deterioration. With a 550lb static load strength, they outperform regular stock shoelaces and handle recurrent exposure to harsh conditions. The low-stretch nylon fabrication ensures knots hold in place, meaning fewer adjustments and more comfortable movement. Featuring a kernmantle design, they are fabricated from 9 removable inner nylon strands enclosed by a woven nylon sheath and capped with 4mm black metal aglets that help prevent frayed ends. Compatible with most brands of hiking boots, running shoes, work boots, and combat boots, these unisex laces also double as versatile survival gear: build a snare, make a sling, extract fishing line, hang a hammock, and more. Whether you're a backcountry adventurer, family camper, or weekend trail seeker, these 550 paracord shoelaces are an easy addition to your outdoor gear.",
            "is_required": true,
            "source": "ai",
            "model": "claude-opus-4-8"
        },
